complex.translation[0].definitions[0].de: consisting of many different parts and often difficult to understand
complex.translation[0].definitions[0].ex: Photosynthesis is a highly complex process.
Peter seemed to have an instant understanding of the most complex issues.
It was a very complex relationship between two complex people.
complex.translation[0].definitions[1].de: a complex word or sentence contains a main part and one or more other parts
complex.translation[1].definitions[0].de: a group of buildings, or a large building with many parts, used for a particular purpose
complex.translation[1].definitions[0].ex: The town has one of the best leisure complexes in the country.
complex.translation[1].definitions[1].de: an emotional problem in which someone is unnecessarily anxious about something or thinks too much about something
complex.translation[1].definitions[1].ex: I used to have a complex about my looks.
complex.translation[1].note_box[0].secti: The new leisure complex includes a swimming pool, a sauna and a gym.

The lively holiday complex has plenty of nightclubs, bars, and restaurants.
